  "response": "To create a typewriter-style font for poems or text on Instagram, people typically use one of these methods:\n\n1. Third-party apps:\n- Fonts Generator\n- Cool Fonts\n- Font Keyboard\n- Stylish Text\nThese apps let you copy and paste typewriter-like text\n\n2. Online font generators:\n- IGfonts.io\n- LingoJam\n- FontGenerator.io\nThese websites provide typewriter-style fonts you can copy\n\n3. Unicode special characters:\nSome typewriter-like fonts are created using special Unicode characters that look like typewriter text\n\n4. Instagram text formatting:\n- Use the built-in text formatting tools\n- Choose a clean, monospaced font\n- Adjust spacing manually\n\n5. External editing apps:\n- Canva\n- Over\n- PicsArt\nThese apps have text styling options for creating typewriter effects\n\nPro tips:\n- Copy and paste fonts\n- Preview before posting\n- Experiment with different styles\n- Ensure readability\n\nMost people use copy-paste methods from font generator websites or apps for the easiest typewriter text effect on Instagram.",
